reviewText: This dvd gives the history and some background of WWII B-24 wreckage of Lady Be Good found in Libya.  This was the air-crew's first combat mission during which they went to Naples and attempted to return to Soluch, Libya at night.  For some reason they overflew the airfield and continued into the desert until they ran out of fuel.  It was assumed they had gone down in the Med and the aircraft was found by oil company personnel, which started a long investigation.
